article.description:
The Seattle SuperSonics are running out of time,
making the most of what little remains.
article.headline: Sonics 2½ games behind Suns for playoff spot
article.linkText: Sonics continue playoff push with victory over Bulls
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- The Seattle SuperSonics are running out of time, making the most of what little remains.
 
Lewis
Rashard Lewis scored 26 points and Ray Allen added 26 points and 13 rebounds as the Seattle Supersonics defeated the Chicago Bulls 101-94 in overtime Tuesday night. Winning for the seventh time in nine games, the Sonics moved ahead of Golden State in the Pacific Division while remaining 2½ games behind the Phoenix Suns for the final playoff spot in the West. Brent Barry hit a desperation 3-pointer from just inside the halfcourt line to help secure the victory. As the shot clock got down to two, Barry hit a desperation shot to give the Sonics a 97-91 lead with 30 seconds left in overtime. "The shot clock was at 3 and I heard the coaches hollering to shoot it and there was no time to pass," said Barry, who previously put up an airball that Elden Campbell rebounded and fired back to Barry. "The shot I attempted previously was so bad I was bound to make something." Barry scored seven points in overtime and Lewis added five. Eddy Curry led Chicago with 28 points and 15 rebounds. Jamal Crawford added a career-high 25 points and eight assists. Seattle had trouble containing Curry in the first half. "At one point in the first quarter I felt unstoppable," said Curry. "I always feel if I get the ball low, if you don't foul me I am going to score." Chicago is 23-14 at home, and the Sonics found out firsthand how tough it can be to win at the United Center. Chicago fought its way back from a 13-point third-quarter deficit, tying the game at 69 on Crawford's jumper with 9:45 left. Donyell Marshall gave the Bulls their first lead of the second half on a putback to make it 81-80 with 3:36 left. Jalen Rose extended the lead to 83-80 on a jumper. Campbell had a tip-in to tie the game at 87 with 59 seconds left. Rose missed a driving layup with two seconds left, and Lewis missed a jumper as time expired in regulation. Crawford scored 11 of his points in the third quarter. The Sonics erased a poor first-quarter effort by closing out the second quarter outscoring the Bulls 17-2. "These guys are obviously a better team at home," said Barry. "They jumped on us early and we had to fight." Lewis scored 11 points during the span. Seattle led 45-40 at the half after trailing by as many as 11. Game notes
Seven of Seattle's last nine games are against teams already in the playoffs or fighting for a spot. ... Bulls F Tyson Chandler missed the game with an inflamed esophagus. He will be out at least a week. ... Curry has led the Bulls in scoring and rebounding in the last three games. ... Allen tied a career-high in rebounds. ... Chicago is 0-7 in overtime games.
